<h3 class="date"><a href="/2006/dec/07/">&#x27a0;</a> December 7, 2006</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="bs_1363_wikiped" >

        
        <a name="003158"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BS_1363">BS 1363 - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</a></h4>

        

        <p>The awesomeness that *is* the British 3-Pin Plug.  The article covers most of the beautiful design decisions, such as the longer earth pin (so earth is the first connection made when you plug it in) and the cable being attached to the bottom, so you&#8217;re less tempted to pull the plug by yanking the cord.  Well done British Standards chaps!</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
                    Filed under
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/bs1363/">bs1363</a>
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/design/">design</a>
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/electrickery/">electrickery</a>
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/uk/">uk</a>
                    
                
            </div>
            <div class="span2" style="text-align: right;">
                
                
                    
                
                <a rel="bookmark" href="/2006/week/49/#bs_1363_wikiped" title="Permanent link to this entry">&#x2732;</a>
